<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1914-11-14T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1914-11-14T00:00:00-05:00" n="1304" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1304">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 855.48/40</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Great Britain</hi> (<persName corresp="#p_PWH1" type="from"><hi rend="italic">Page</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                            </hi>
                        </head>
                        <dateline>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">American Embassy</hi>, <lb/>
                            <placeName>
                                <hi rend="italic">London</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1914-11-14">
                                <hi rend="italic">November 14, 1914</hi>.</date>
                        </dateline>
                        <p rend="center">[Telegram]</p>
                        <p>1060. Since the report seems to be widely circulated in the United States
                            that the German military authorities in Belgium are stopping food for
                            the needy Belgians, it may seem to you wise to contradict the report.
                            There has been no interference. In appearance, the German military
                            authorities give useful assistance.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">American Ambassador</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>